{"type":"message","id":"dd1e3ebf","parentId":"cfb5a9fd","timestamp":"2026-03-07T14:37:17.149Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to configure myself to use only the local model. Looking at my runtime info, I'm currently running on \"bailian/qwen3.5-plus\" which is a remote model (Alibaba's Qwen). \n\nThe user wants me to use only local models. Looking at the model aliases in my system instructions, I see:\n- qwen3.5-9b-abliterated-vision: ollama/lukey03/qwen3.5-9b-abliterated-vision\n\nThis appears to be a local Ollama model. The user wants me to configure myself to use only local models.\n\nI should use the session_status tool to set a per-session model override to a local model. Looking at the session_status tool description:\n\"Show a /status-equivalent session status card (usage + time + cost when available). Use for model-use questions (📊 session_status). Optional: set per-session model override (model=default resets overrides).\"\n\nSo I can use session_status with model parameter to set an override. For local-only, I should use an Ollama model. Let me set it to the ollama model.\n\nActually, looking more carefully - the session_status tool is primarily for showing status, but it has an optional model parameter that can set per-session model override. The description says \"model=default resets overrides\" which implies other values set overrides.\n\nLet me set the model to a local ollama model. The available local model from the aliases is:\n- ollama/lukey03/qwen3.5-9b-abliterated-vision\n\nI'll use session_status to set this override.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4940d353164d45caa3c0abe3","name":"session_status","arguments":{"model":"ollama/lukey03/qwen3.5-9b-abliterated-vision"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"qwen3.5-plus","usage":{"input":21143,"output":742,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21885,"cost":{"input":0,"output"