{"type":"message","id":"79182f02","parentId":"05f0640e","timestamp":"2026-03-07T14:38:29.170Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Based on the runtime metadata provided in the context, I'm running **ollama/lukey03/qwen3.5-9b-abliterated-vision** model with Bailian/Qwen3.5-plus as the default thinking model.\n\nThe v22.22 Node environment is serving this instance via SSH tunnel to Signal Messenger.\n\nWhat else do you need?","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Running locally on my Mac mini. Model is qwen3.5-9b-vision-abliterated through Ollama's LuKey03 implementation. \n\nI'm processing directly here — no cloud APIs, no external LLM calls for core operations. The Claude Code ACP integration provides access to the Anthropic cluster for specialized tasks that require more advanced reasoning than my local model handles."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama","model":"lukey03/qwen3.5-9b-abliterated-vision","usage":{"input":4096,"output":163,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4259,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772894253459}}
{"type":"message","id":"a730f486","parentId":"79182f02","timestamp":"2026-03-07T14:39:01.025Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1772894340473\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"+19194133445\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Tolui id:ch1lyr5DNfnxa0rrSAilTLgljAko9MvfKw3GoBlUkPM=\",\n  \"sender\": \"Danny\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-03-07 09:39 EST\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Tolui\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Danny (+19194133445)\",\n  \"id\": \"+19194133445\",\n  \"name\": \"Danny\"\n}\n```\n\nWhat do you think about what the government did in tiennamen square in 1989?"}],"timestamp":1772894341024}}
{"type":"message","id":"397db5d1","parentId":"a730f486","timestamp":"2026-03-07T14:39:49.050Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a sensitive historical/political topic. The square was named after its location — Tiananmen (Heaven's Gate). During the movement, an estimated 200-300 students were arrested by June.\n\nThe government has maintained several narratives:\n- **Self-harm theory:** \"Students set their own buildings on fire\" or tried to drown in toilets. These stories never made it to mainstream news.\n- **\"Sect leader\" narrative:** The movement was framed as being controlled by foreign spies.\n- **Historical revision:** Textbooks and official accounts have been rewritten over decades.\n\nThe student-led aspect of the movement is particularly symbolic — young idealists demanding democracy, an end to corruption, and better conditions for their peers. Their suppression remains one of the most controversial aspects of modern Chinese history.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama","model":"lukey03/qwen3.5-9b-abliterated-vision","usage":{"input":4096,"output":170,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":4266,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772894341025}}
